meanings.definition: To sell more than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The new toy outsells all the other toys in the store.
meanings.sent2: Her lemonade stand always outsells the other kids' stands.
meanings.sent3: The little girl's lemonade stand outsells the big supermarket's drinks!
meanings.sent4: His charm outsells any marketing strategy.
meanings.sent5: The bright sign outside the store outsells all the competitors.

meanings.definition: To be more successful in sales than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: Their bakery outsells all the other bakeries in town.
meanings.sent2: The popular brand outsells all the generic ones.
meanings.sent3: The cat's meow outsells the dog's bark!
meanings.sent4: Her determination outsells any obstacle in her way.
meanings.sent5: The catchy jingle outsells the plain advertisement.
